## 2.3 Shell config timing (major bug risk)

### Problem

Your draft implies shell configs may be written early.

### This will break:

* aliases not yet defined
* git not configured
* paths not finalized
* clipboard helpers missing

### Fix

Split shell module:

#### Phase A — install shells

```text
Install bash/zsh/fish
Choose default shells per user
```

#### Phase B — configure shells (VERY LATE)

```text
Render configs using:
- alias registry
- env registry
- tool detection
```

---

## 2.4 No state system (this will break re-runs)

### Problem

You don’t persist decisions.

### Consequence

* reruns overwrite configs
* modules cannot detect prior state
* no repair mode possible

### Fix

Add:

```text
/var/lib/iosish/state/
```

Files:

```text
users.conf
shells.conf
packages.conf
features.conf
mounts.conf
```

Each module:

* reads state
* updates state
* never assumes fresh system

---

## 2.5 No validation phase

### Problem

Installer ends without verification.

### Fix

Add final module:

```text
Validation & Summary
```

Checks:

* users exist
* shell paths valid
* doas/sudo works
* git identity set
* ssh works
* mounts accessible
* clipboard functional
* aliases loaded

